## ğŸš€ Installation & Setup

### Prerequisites
- Web browser (Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Edge)
- Code editor (VS Code recommended)

### Quick Start
1. Clone the repository:
```bash
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/portfolio.git
cd portfolio
```

2. Open `index.html` in your browser

3. Or use Live Server (VS Code extension):
   - Install "Live Server" extension
   - Right-click on `index.html`
   - Select "Open with Live Server"

### Development Setup
For local development, you can use any HTTP server:

```bash
# Using Python
python -m http.server 8000

# Using Node.js with http-server
npx http-server
```

## ğŸ¨ Customization

### Changing Colors
Edit CSS variables in `css/themes.css`:
```css
:root {
    --primary-color: #3b82f6;
    --secondary-color: #10b981;
    --text-color: #1f2937;
    --background-color: #ffffff;
    /* ... more variables */
}
```

### Adding New Language
1. Add language classes in HTML:
```html
<span class="en">English Text</span>
<span class="fa">Persian Text</span>
<span class="es">Spanish Text</span>
```

2. Update language switcher in `js/language.js`

### Adding New Section
1. Add HTML structure in `index.html`
2. Style it in `css/main.css`
3. Add interactivity in JavaScript if needed

